---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Tree Service News, including how information is collected, used, retained, and protected."
  canonicalPath="/privacy-policy"
>
  <main class="site-main">
    <div style="max-width:760px">
      <h1 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:2.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin-bottom:.5rem">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p style="color:var(--muted); font-size:.9rem; margin-bottom:2rem; padding-bottom:1.5rem; border-bottom:2px solid var(--green)">
        Effective Date: May 11, 2026
      </p>

      <div style="font-size:.975rem; line-height:1.75; color:var(--text)">
        <p>
          Tree Service News ("we," "our," or "us") operates the website located at <a href="https://treeservicenews.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--green); font-weight:600">https://treeservicenews.com</a> and related tools, services, and applications.
        </p>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you visit our website or use our services.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          1. Information We Collect
        </h2>
        <p>We may collect the following types of information:</p>

        <h3 style="font-size:1.05rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:1.25rem 0 .5rem">
          Information you provide directly
        </h3>
        <p>This may include:</p>
        <ul style="margin:0 0 1.5rem; padding-left:1.25rem; display:grid; gap:.35rem">
          <li>Name</li>
          <li>Email address</li>
          <li>Business name</li>
          <li>Website URL</li>
          <li>Social media page information</li>
          <li>Messages or form submissions</li>
          <li>Any information you voluntarily submit through contact forms, signup forms, or connected tools</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="font-size:1.05rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:1.25rem 0 .5rem">
          Information collected automatically
        </h3>
        <p>
          When you visit our website, we may automatically collect basic technical information, including:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin:0 0 1.5rem; padding-left:1.25rem; display:grid; gap:.35rem">
          <li>IP address</li>
          <li>Browser type</li>
          <li>Device type</li>
          <li>Pages visited</li>
          <li>Referring website</li>
          <li>Date and time of visit</li>
          <li>General usage data</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This information may be collected through cookies, analytics tools, server logs, or similar technologies.
        </p>

        <h3 style="font-size:1.05rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:1.25rem 0 .5rem">
          Information from third-party platforms
        </h3>
        <p>
          If you connect a third-party platform, such as Facebook, we may access limited information necessary to provide the requested service. This may include:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin:0 0 1.5rem; padding-left:1.25rem; display:grid; gap:.35rem">
          <li>Facebook Page name</li>
          <li>Facebook Page ID</li>
          <li>Page access permissions granted by you</li>
          <li>Content selected or submitted for posting</li>
          <li>Basic account or business information provided through Meta's platform</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We only access information that you authorize through the third-party platform.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          2. How We Use Information
        </h2>
        <p>We may use collected information to:</p>
        <ul style="margin:0 0 1.5rem; padding-left:1.25rem; display:grid; gap:.35rem">
          <li>Provide and operate our website and services</li>
          <li>Respond to inquiries</li>
          <li>Publish or schedule content when authorized by you</li>
          <li>Improve website performance and user experience</li>
          <li>Monitor website traffic and usage</li>
          <li>Maintain security and prevent abuse</li>
          <li>Communicate updates related to our services</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information.</p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          3. Facebook and Meta Platform Data
        </h2>
        <p>
          If you authorize our app through Facebook or Meta, we may use granted permissions to help publish or manage content on Facebook Pages you control.
        </p>
        <p>
          We only use Facebook-related data for the purpose of providing the functionality you requested, such as posting content to an authorized Facebook Page.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not sell Facebook data, share it with unauthorized third parties, or use it for unrelated advertising purposes.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may revoke access at any time through your Facebook account settings.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          4. Cookies and Analytics
        </h2>
        <p>
          Our website may use cookies or similar technologies to improve functionality, analyze website traffic, and understand how visitors use the site.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can disable cookies through your browser settings, but some parts of the website may not function properly.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          5. Third-Party Services
        </h2>
        <p>
          We may use third-party services for hosting, analytics, forms, email, social media integrations, or other business operations.
        </p>
        <p>
          These third-party providers may process information according to their own privacy policies.
        </p>
        <p>Examples may include:</p>
        <ul style="margin:0 0 1.5rem; padding-left:1.25rem; display:grid; gap:.35rem">
          <li>Website hosting providers</li>
          <li>Analytics tools</li>
          <li>Email service providers</li>
          <li>Meta/Facebook services</li>
          <li>Form or automation tools</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          6. Data Retention
        </h2>
        <p>
          We retain information only as long as reasonably necessary to provide our services, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and maintain business records.
        </p>
        <p>
          Facebook or Meta-related data is retained only as long as needed to provide the connected service or until you request deletion.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          7. Data Deletion Requests
        </h2>
        <p>
          You may request deletion of your personal information or Facebook-related data by contacting us at:
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="mailto:privacy@treeservicenews.com" style="color:var(--green); font-weight:600">privacy@treeservicenews.com</a>
        </p>
        <p>Please include enough information for us to identify your request.</p>
        <p>
          You may also remove our app's access from your Facebook account settings.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          8. Data Security
        </h2>
        <p>
          We use reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures to protect information from unauthorized access, misuse, loss, or disclosure.
        </p>
        <p>
          However, no online system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          9. Children's Privacy
        </h2>
        <p>
          Our website and services are not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          10. Your Rights
        </h2>
        <p>
          Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict the use of your personal information.
        </p>
        <p>
          To make a request, contact us at:
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="mailto:privacy@treeservicenews.com" style="color:var(--green); font-weight:600">privacy@treeservicenews.com</a>
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          11. Changes to This Policy
        </h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.
        </p>

        <h2 style="font-family:var(--serif); font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--black); margin:2rem 0 .75rem">
          12. Contact Us
        </h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at:</p>
        <p>
          Tree Service News<br />
          Rocinante Marketing LLC<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:jj@rocinantemarketing.com" style="color:var(--green); font-weight:600">jj@rocinantemarketing.com</a><br />
          Website: <a href="https://treeservicenews.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--green); font-weight:600">https://treeservicenews.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
